itemListElement.name: Yoga Trapeze Aerial Yoga class at Gravity Yoga

name: Yoga Trapeze Aerial Yoga class at Gravity Yoga
description: Come to Gravity Yoga LLC to experience a unique style of yoga; Yoga Trapeze. Our classes are open to beginners to yoga and experienced yogis. Class is one hour and runs very much like a regular yoga session. We start by warming up and tuning into our breathing. We then move using the Yoga Trapeze to support our postures. Ending the class with a savasana in the Trapeze. Students leave feeling stretched, worked out, & relaxed. It is a fun way to spend time with friends and family. Usually there is a perfect mix of focus and fun. There is a small amount of risk taking which can be exciting and fun to do with those you know or want to know better. While many of the yoga poses we do on the Yoga Trapeze look very similar to their mat-based counterparts, the dynamics are very unique.

itemListElement.name: Seattle City Scavenger Hunt by Zombie Scavengers

name: Seattle City Scavenger Hunt by Zombie Scavengers
description: Walk around Seattle while trying to survive the zombie apocalypse with Zombie Scavengers! On an app, you'll be given a list of items to find (in any order you choose) to help you survive a zombie apocalypse. You'll get points for finding these items, as well as completing some zombie themed challenges. Figure out the best game plan to get the most points in order to survive. A remote host will chat with you during the game if you have any questions. Prove you can survive the zombie apocalypse in Seattle for bragging rights with all your friends!

itemListElement.name: OLD - Operation City Quest Scavenger Hunt - Seattle, WA

name: OLD - Operation City Quest Scavenger Hunt - Seattle, WA
description: Using an app on your smartphone, you'll be given nearly 150 objects to find during your scavenger hunt. You'll then wander throughout the downtown area searching for the items. Once you've found the object, you'll send a photo in to score points. Along the way, you will perform challenges and answer trivia questions for even more points. You'll have 15+ categories of objects you can find in this city walk, with each object varying in points depending on the difficulty. Don't worry, you won't be alone. You'll have a remote guide that will be texting you during your game if you need help or have a question. They will also encourage you and give you hints along the way! The objective of the game is to have fun, rank #1 on the leaderboard, and try to get as many points as possible by finding all of the objects!

name: Seattle Post-Cruise Tour Package
description: End your cruise adventure in Seattle with this award-winning tour package!  We'll whisk you (and your luggage) from the cruise pier on a 3 hour City Highlights Tour in our comfy 14 passenger mini-coach led by an entertaining and knowledgable local guide, finishing with a drop-off at the airport or your hotel.  From the perfect selfie viewpoint to historic landmarks and quirky neighborhoods, this tour is a convenient and fun way to discover what makes Seattle such a beautiful and unique city.

review.name: See Seattle with Matthew
review.reviewBody: Matthew, the singing 🎶 tour guide, was the best EVER! We had already toured Seattle on our own, so almost didn’t even schedule this, but we had a few hours to kill and needed transportation to the airport from the cruise terminal. Matthew texted early that morning to confirm and to update on details of his arrival to pick us up. He took us to all the places and in a very entertaining way gave us information on each destination. We made stops at the best viewpoints(Kerry Park, Queen Anne Lake Union, Fremont Troll, Fisherman’s Wharf, Salmon Bay Waterway, Pike Place Market …) and he offered to take pictures of us at each one. We drove through China Town saw Amazon Sphere, Lumen Field and so much more. If  you have a later flight, he gives the option of adding on extended time at pike and the space needle. He dropped us at the airport while those who were doing the extended tour stayed at Pike. We have been on many tours and I definitely rate this one at the very top. After he took our pictures, I found his selfie of him on my phone. 😂 He was so much fun! **********

review.name: Summer in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Driver Mark was very friendly and knowledgeable. We went to various parts of Seattle.we weren't able to get out at Pike market but we were taken to the airport

review.name: Tour Guide Spencer was the Best!!
review.reviewBody: This is a "Must Do "for a fantastic opportunity to learn about Seattle.  I have been there many times and thought I knew a lot but our Tour Guide Spencer  went above and beyond.  He is a native who loves his city and thrives on making every stop memorable.  He actually laid on the ground and took our pictures on our phones so we could have the entire Space Needle in the background. He is a great ambassador for Seattle!

review.name: A great way to experience Seattle!
review.reviewBody: We had just returned from an Alaskan 7 day cruise, I a can honestly say that this tour was better than ANY of the cruise activities!  Matthew was our tour guide and his background in theatre treated us to some excellent history, story telling, narration and even an occasional relevant show tune delivered beautifully (and my husband doesn't even like musicals!). We had 10 participants, and the pick up was smooth and on time.  We made several stops for leg stretching, pictures and bathroom stops, and Matthew was so helpful with getting pictures and accommodating our preferences. At the end of the 3 1/2 hour tour, a few participants were dropped off right at the airport, and we were then dropped off at our hotel near the airport while awaiting our red-eye flight. We had a great time, and this was well worth the investment!

review.name: Post cruise tour of Seatle
review.reviewBody: The tour was very nice. Our tour guide Matthew was informative and entertaining. We seen so many things in Seattle that we would never would have known were there. Many beautiful pictures of the area. Glad we were able to see and learn about Seatle after our amazing cruise.

review.name: See you in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide James was awesome .He was extremely knowledgeable with a great sense of humor. I would highly recommend him . Easy peasy pick up at the cruise terminal

review.name: Seattle Post cruise tour
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful tour of Seattle after our cruise. Our tour guide was Matthew Posner and he was simply amazing.  He knew facts and trivia about Seattle that was mind boggling!  The best part of it is that he sang to us!  He has an amazing singing voice as he was in theater for many years!  What a wonderful day to see Seattle sites and be sang to along the way.  Thank you Matthew  for an amazing experience!

review.name: Seattle with Matthew, the Singing Tour Guide, :-)
review.reviewBody: OK, after getting off of a cruise ship in Seattle and needing to spend the day doing something more interesting than sitting at the airport for our redeye back to the East Coast, we booked this tour, with extension, and had the joy of spending a good part of the day with "Matthew the Singing Tour Guide."  He is an engaging, knowledgeable, guide, and made the time well worth it.  We would book this again without hesitation!!

review.name: Best post cruise tour
review.reviewBody: Matthew the singing tour guide was the best. Very entertaining and knowledgeable. Got us to the airport post tour in plenty of time.

review.name: Fun way to end vacation
review.reviewBody: Matthew, the singing tour guide, treated us to some sights we've never seen before. Easy pick-up at the port and drop-off at the airport. Plenty of fun stops, with entertainment and interesting tidbits of information along the way. Matthew made the tour a fun way to end our vacation!

The coffee bar features varieties from Fonté's Special Selection Series, roasted at its own facility in Seattle's Georgetown neighborhood.

Hard Rock Cafe Seattle
description: Opened February 10, 2010, just steps from the iconic Pike Place Market entrance, Hard Rock Cafe Seattle resides in a restored century-old building, with the original timber beams intact and on display. With three floors - including a rooftop terrace with beautiful views of the Market and Sound, a second-floor private event space and live music venue, a spacious main-floor dining room, and one-of-a-kind Seattle music memorabilia on display throughout - we have something to suit almost every need. Whether joining us for a delicious Legendary Burger and an ice-cold brew, seeing an up-and-coming band perform an intimate set, or hosting your next corporate event on our rooftop, Hard Rock Seattle's dedicated team has you covered. Give us a ring today to reserve your table, or for more information on live music shows or private event bookings. Everyone is a VIP here, and treated accordingly. Love All, Serve All.
